(Docker → Nexus Push)
🔹 STEP 1: Create Docker Repo in Nexus
Go to Nexus UI → Repositories
Create → Docker (hosted)

Set:

Name: docker-hosted
Port: 8084 ✅ (IMPORTANT)
Deployment: Allow redeploy

👉 Your Docker registry:

http://<IP>:8084
🔹 STEP 2: Enable Docker Login
Go to Security → Realms
Enable:
Docker Bearer Token Realm
🔹 STEP 3: Configure Docker for HTTP (VERY IMPORTANT)

Because Nexus runs on HTTP, fix this:

Edit:

sudo vi /etc/docker/daemon.json

Add:

{
  "insecure-registries": ["<IP>:8084"]
}

Restart:

sudo systemctl restart docker
🔹 STEP 4: Login to Nexus
docker login <IP>:8084

❌ NOT 8082
✅ ALWAYS use 8084

🔹 STEP 5: Tag Your Image

Your image:

java3-war-app

Tag it:

docker tag java3-war-app <IP>:8084/java3-war-app:latest
🔹 STEP 6: Push Image
docker push <IP>:8084/java3-war-app:latest
🔹 STEP 7: Verify
Nexus → Browse → docker-hosted
You’ll see image
🔥 CLEAN SUMMARY (1 LINE FLOW)
create repo (8084) → enable realm → insecure registry → login → tag → push
